==English==
===Noun===
'''[[government]] [[man]]'''
# A representative of the [[government]].
# A supporter of the [[government]].
# {{AU}} {{obsolete}} {{euphemism}} In the days when Australia was a penal colony: a [[convict]].
#: 1888: ''Whatever it was that had happened to him in the old times when he was a Government man he didn’t talk about.'' &mdash; [[w:Rolf Boldrewood|Rolf Boldrewood]], ''Robbery Under Arms'' [http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/1198]
===Usage notes===
The term [[convict]] was considered an insult in early colonial Australia, ''government man'' was the approved euphemism (reference: [[w:Robert Hughes|Robert Hughes]], ''The Fatal Shore'', 1987, paperback ISBN 1-86046-150-6, page xi.).  See [[convict]] for other terms.
